OL,6,FThose without their own home, but
OL,7,Fstaying with relatives or friends, on
OL,8,Fsofas or in cars have often never
OL,9,Fengaged with statutory bodies, meaning
OL,10,Fthey are invisible to the system.
OL,12,FThe new research showed that 37% of
OL,13,Fpeople experiencing hidden
OL,14,Fhomelessness have been left in that
OL,15,Fsituation due to the loss of a private
OL,16,Frental property.
OL,18,FJustin, 23, knows all to well what
OL,19,Fit's like to sofa-surf.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/12
